# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for the publish pipeline and supply-chain surface.
#
# GitHub's CODEOWNERS enforces required review on PRs touching these paths
# (requires "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection on `main`).
# Even if a bot workflow or prompt-injection attack pushes a change to these
# files, the PR cannot merge without owner approval.
#
# Protected categories:
#   - CI / release workflows (ci.yml, e2e-aca.yml, cleanup-runs.yml)
#   - Dockerfiles (backend-ts, web-nextjs, microservice base)
#   - Azure infra (Terraform that provisions ACR, ACA apps, Key Vault, Postgres)
#   - Dependency-automation config (renovate.json, .mise.toml)
#   - Env template (.env.example) — contributes to Key Vault seed values

# CI/CD infrastructure
.github/**                         @AndriyKalashnykov

# All Dockerfiles (prod + dev)
**/Dockerfile                      @AndriyKalashnykov
**/Dockerfile.*                    @AndriyKalashnykov
**/docker-compose.yaml             @AndriyKalashnykov
**/docker-compose.yml              @AndriyKalashnykov

# Azure Terraform — governs ACR, ACA, Key Vault, Postgres, Dapr components
infra/**                           @AndriyKalashnykov

# Dependency automation + toolchain pins
renovate.json                      @AndriyKalashnykov
.mise.toml                         @AndriyKalashnykov

# Secrets template (seeds Key Vault via Terraform)
.env.example                       @AndriyKalashnykov

